OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNigeria police to stop     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsacking unwed pregnant     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fstaff                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A rule banning unmarried Nigerian      
OL,6, police officers from getting pregnant  
OL,7, and ensured their sacking if they did, 
OL,8, has been scrapped.                     
OL,10,FIn a landmark case, a judge ruled the  
OL,11,Fregulation was discriminatory as it did
OL,12,Fnot apply to male officers who got     
OL,13,Fco-workers pregnant.                   
OL,15,FThe case was brought by a corporal who 
OL,16,Fwas sacked in 2021 after getting       
OL,17,Fpregnant.                              
OL,19,FThe woman was awarded 5m naira (#9,100)
OL,20,Fin compensation.                       
